Popular Yoruba activist, Sunday Adeyemo, (Igboho) has debunked the report which claimed he had been arrested by operatives of the Department of State Services. Reports claim that the Yoruba Nation agitator was arrested with the founder of the One Love Family, Satguru Maharaj Ji, on Friday. Sunday Igboho But in an audio shared by Igboho's aide, Olayomi Koiki, the agitator noted that he was not arrested by the DSS but is currently in his house at Ibadan. Igboho, while speaking on the report making the rounds about his arrest, appreciated his fans and followers across the world for their support. The Yoruba activist, who stated that he heard that he was arrested at Guru Maharaj Ji, claimed that he is nowhere around the reported location but back in his house in Ibadan.



